\par ALUMISTEEL (PL 5)
\par }{This easy-to-acquire alloy is lightweight and reasonably strong. Alumisteel can also be used for armor (see Mecha Armor, below).
\par }{\b Hardness: }{10.
\par }{\b Base Purchase DC Modifier: }{\endash 4.
\par }{\b 
\par DURALLOY (PL 6)
\par }{Duralloy is harder, heavier, and more durable than alumisteel. It can also be used to fashion armor (see Mecha Armor, below).
\par }{\b Hardness: }{15.
\par }{\b Base Purchase DC Modifier: }{None.
\par }{\b 
\par VANADIUM (PL 6)
\par }{Vanadium alloy absorbs a respectable amount of damage and is easy to mold.
\par }{\b Hardness: }{20.
\par }{\b Base Purchase DC Modifier: }{+4.
\par }{\b 
\par NEOVULCANIUM (PL 7)
\par }{Similar to duralloy, neovulcanium uses plasma-forging techniques to create an alloy of unparalleled resilience. Neovulcanium can also be used for armor (see Mecha Armor, below).
