\b Normal Damage: }{The attack deals normal damage (do not apply critical hit multipliers).
\par }{\b Crew Dazed: }{Each crewmember aboard the mecha, including its operator, must succeed on a Fortitude save (DC 15) or be dazed for 1 round. Unable to act, a dazed character can take no actions, but still retains his or her full Defense.
\par }{\b Normal Critical Hit: }{Roll critical hit damage normally.
\par }{\b Mecha Knocked Prone: }{The force of the attack knocks the mecha prone. All crewmembers and passengers aboard take 1d6 points of bludgeoning damage as they are knocked about their cockpits. A prone mecha takes a \endash 
4 penalty on melee attack rolls and can\rquote t use thrown ranged weapons. The mecha gains a +4 bonus to Defense against ranged attacks, but takes a \endash 4 penalty to Defense against melee attacks.
\par Standing up from prone is a move action that provokes attacks of opportunity.
\par }{\b Mecha Stunned: }{The mecha automatically drops what it is holding and can take no attack or move actions for 1 round. While the mecha is stunned, apply a \endash 2 penalty to the mecha operator\rquote 
s Defense (even though the operator is not stunned).
\par }{\b Severe Critical Hit: }{Roll critical hit damage using a x5 multiplier instead of the weapon\rquote s normal multiplier.
\par }{\b Crew Hit: }{The attack bypasses the mecha\rquote s armor and superstructure. Apply normal damage to one crewmember or passenger (determined randomly), ignoring the mecha\rquote s bonus hit points.
\par }{\b Equipment Destroyed: }{One piece of equipment (attacker\rquote s choice) is damaged and ceases
 to function until repaired. It can be a flight system, sensor system, defense system, weapon (handheld or integrated), or miscellaneous system. Repairing a damaged system requires 1 hour of work and a successful Repair check (DC 20).
\par }{\b Equipment Destroyed: }{One piece of equipment (attacker\rquote 
s choice) is destroyed and ceases to function. It can be a flight system, sensor system, defense system, weapon (handheld or integrated), or miscellaneous system. A destroyed system cannot be repaired, only replaced.
\par }{\b Slot Damaged: }{One of the mecha\rquote s equipment slots (attacker\rquote 
s choice) is damaged. Any piece of equipment wholly or partially installed in that slot will not function until the slot is repaired. Repairing a damaged equipment slot requires 1 hour of work and a successful Repair check (DC 25).
\par }{\b Slot Destroyed: }{One of the mecha\rquote s equipment slots (attacker\rquote s choice) is destroyed, along with any piece of equipment wholly or partially installed in it. Rebuilding a destroyed equipment slot requires 12 hours of work and a s
uccessful Craft (mechanical) check (DC 30).
\par }{\fs24 
\par RANGED ATTACKS AND ATTACKS OF OPPORTUNITY
\par }{Mecha only provoke attacks of opportunity from creatures of their own size or larger (including other mecha) when they fire a ranged weapon in a threatened area.
\par }{\fs24 
\par STOWING HAND SLOT EQUIPMENT
\par }{Any piece of mecha equipment integrated into a mecha\rquote s hand slot\emdash and only the hand slot\emdash 
can be stowed magnetically against the mecha or in a storage compartment as a move action. This frees up the hand to perform more delicate manipulation (such as opening a door or pressing a button) or grabbing another piece of mecha equipment.
\par A mecha may have more pieces of equipment for its hand slots than it has hand slots available; it just can\rquote t use them all at once.
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel1\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs36 
