\par }{\b Benefit: }{Choose a size of mecha (Large, Huge, Gargantuan, or Colossal). When you are operati
ng a mecha of the chosen size, you gain a +1 dodge bonus to Defense. Furthermore, armor penalties for operating the mecha are 2 less than they would otherwise be (minimum penalty \endash 0).
\par }{\fs24 
\par HAIR TRIGGER
\par }{You have developed a delicate sense of timing, and your area attacks hit your foes when they\rquote re ill-prepared to defend against them.
\par }{\b Prerequisite: }{Base attack bonus +6.
\par }{\b Benefit: }{Whenever you make an attack from your mecha that requires enemies to make Reflex saving throws, the DC for such saves is increased by +2.
\par }{\fs24 
\par MECHA CRUSH
\par }{You can hurl your mecha\rquote s body onto opponents to deal tremendous damage.
\par }{\b Prerequisite: }{Mecha Operation.
\par }{\b Benefit: }{As an attack action, you can maneuver your mecha to jump or fall onto opponents, using the mecha\rquote s body to crush them. This atta
ck is useful only against creatures at least two size categories smaller than your mecha. The base damage for a crush attack depends on your mecha\rquote 
s size category, as given below. Add 1.5 times your mecha-modified Strength bonus to this base damage to determine the total damage for the attack.
