\par }{\b Benefit: }{When you attempt to overrun an opponent while operating a mecha, the target may not choose to avoid your mecha. If your me
cha knocks down the target, your mecha may make one free slam attack against the target, gaining a +4 bonus on the attack roll because the target is prone.
\par }{\fs24 
\par MECHA WEAPON BOOST
\par }{By disabling safeguards and shunting auxiliary power into your weapons, you can attain greater destructive power at the cost of weapon accuracy.
\par }{\b Prerequisite: }{Base attack bonus +8, Repair 6 ranks.
\par }{\b Benefit: }{You can take a penalty of up to \endash 5 on your attack roll. If you do, the mecha weapon of your choice deals +1d6 points of damage for each \endash 
1 penalty you took. The attack penalty persists until the beginning of your next turn, but the additional damage applies only to the next single attack you make.
\par }{\fs24 
\par MECHA WEAPON PROFICIENCY
\par }{You know how to acquire targets and fire your mecha\rquote s weapons using onboard computers and sensors.
\par }{\b Prerequisite: }{Mecha Operation.
\par }{\b Benefit: }{You no longer suffer the standard penalties on attack rolls while you\rquote re in your mecha. You can use any feats that refer to firearms with your ranged mecha weapons.
\par }{\b Normal: }{Characters without this feat take a \endash 4 penalty on attack rolls made while in a mecha cockpit. Furthermore, they cannot apply firearm feats to a mecha\rquote s ranged weapons.
\par }{\fs24 
\par STUN MECHA
\par }{By channeling electricity into an enemy mecha\rquote s control system, you can temporarily short it out.
\par }{\b Prerequisite: }{Base attack bonus +8, Mecha Operation, Precise Shot.
\par }{\b Benefit: }{If you threaten a critical hit with an electricity attack against another mecha, you may automatically confirm the critical. In addition to suffering the effects o
f the critical hit, the mecha is automatically stunned for 2d4 rounds. The stunned mecha automatically drops what it is holding and can take no attack or move actions. While the mecha is stunned, apply a \endash 2 penalty to the mecha operator\rquote 
s Defense (even though the operator is not stunned).
\par }{\fs24 
\par THRUSTER BLAST
\par }{By directing your vectored thrusters all around your mecha, you can kick up a cloud of dust and debris that obscures the battlefield.
\par }{\b Prerequisite: }{Pilot 10 ranks, mecha flight system (either jetpack, thruster boots, or ramjet thruster boots).
\par }{\b Benefit: }{You can aim your thruster exhaust toward the ground to create a hemispherical cloud. If you are within 30 feet of the ground and there is loose debris or dust, you can create a cloud with a 50-foot radius cent
ered directly below you. The generated winds snuff out small fires and give guided missiles attacking you a \endash 
4 penalty on their attack rolls. Creatures without eye protection caught within the debris cloud are blinded while inside it and for 1 round after 
emerging from it. The debris cloud grants anyone inside it one-half concealment (20% miss chance). Mecha with sensor systems ignore the concealment effects.
\par Because some mecha have vectored thrust systems, their flight path isn\rquote t affected by the aim of the exhaust. They don\rquote t have to hover or fly upward to create the cloud.
